    "extras": [
      "Book Frida Kahlo Museum tickets and Isla Mujeres ferries a few days ahead in high season — same-day slots sell out fast.",
      "ADO buses are the most reliable overland option in the Yucatán; book early morning departures for cooler travel and better seat choice.",
      "Carry some cash for markets, colectivos, cenotes, and small mezcalerías even though cards work in most hotels and museums.",
      "Uber works well in Mexico City and Mérida, while DiDi is a handy backup; Cancún airport transfers are usually smoother when pre-booked.",
      "Dry season runs best overall, but December and Easter are expensive enough that shoulder-season November or late January often feels better value."
    ],
